<item>
            <title>[SPARK-52355] VariantVal schema improperly inferred as struct&lt;metadata:binary,value:binary&gt;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-52355</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When creating VariantVal objects locally in Python, the schema is improperly inferred as a struct with metadata and value fields.&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; from pyspark.sql.types import VariantVal&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; df = spark.createDataFrame([(VariantVal.parseJson(&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&quot;),)], schema=&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;#39;value&amp;#39;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; df.printSchema()&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;root&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;|-- value: struct (nullable = true)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;| |-- metadata: binary (nullable = true)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;| |-- value: binary (nullable = true)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; df.collect()&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Row(value=Row(metadata=bytearray(b&amp;#39;\x01\x00\x00&amp;#39;), value=bytearray(b&amp;#39;\x03\x01\x00\x02\x0c\x01&amp;#39;)))&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When the schema is passed explicitly, everything works as intended&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; from pyspark.sql.types import VariantVal&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; df = spark.createDataFrame([(VariantVal.parseJson(&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&quot;),)], schema=&apos;value variant&apos;)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; df.printSchema()&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;root&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;|-- value: variant (nullable = true)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; df.collect()&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Row(value=VariantVal(bytearray(b&amp;#39;\x03\x01\x00\x02\x0c\x01&amp;#39;), bytearray(b&amp;#39;\x01\x00\x00&amp;#39;)))&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; df.collect()&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;.value.toJson()&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;&apos;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&apos;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This appears to be because the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/e3321aa44ea255365222c491657b709ef41dc460/python/pyspark/sql/types.py#L2178-L2322&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;tt&gt;pyspark.sql.type._infer_type&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/a&gt; function does not include a case for VariantVal objects&lt;/p&gt;</description>
